It wasn’t 5 minutes when the general manager pulled his vehicle next to mine ready to lend a hand. I honestly can’t recall his name. He gave my car a jump start and my car started right away. I have been purchasing  food from Sardi's , [ocated in  Bowie, Maryland, for two years.  And, for the record, let me just be honest, I would wholeheartedly recommend this restaurant to anyone, looking for a wonderful place to eat.  When my family or friends come to town, or on the weekends, after completing our weekend tasks, we would go to Sardi's, either for lunch or dinner. The chickens are  always fresh, well seasoned,, tender, not dry, and you get more than you can eat in one seating.  We always end up taking home leftovers, for the following day.  It doesn't matter whether it's chicken, beef, pork chops, or steaks, let me just say, without reservation, that everything is cooked to perfection.  And, let's not forget the vegetables.  They are also well seasoned, not overcooked or dry.  Together,  if you are looking for a place to get an absolute wonderful meal, Sardi's is the place.  However, no restaurant would not be great without the outstanding services rendered by staff members working together such as Alex, Dominin, and Luis, just to name a few.  Let me just say that the entire staff in Sardi's, located at the Bowie Town Center,  are all outstanding, and I, as well as my family, friends, and co-workers will continue to support Sardi's.  It's just that delicious, and a great place to enjoy delicious food, as well as the excellent service.

I am not above being “That Guy” that makes a deliberate effort (while everyone looks at me shaking their head) to select the LEAST CHARRED chicken available. Sardi's is a chain and with that they pump out fast, quick, quality food. I ordered two lunch specials which come with fries/coleslaw/half chicken/soda for $11. The deal is pretty decent but none of the sides looked appetizing. Fries were a dry and coleslaw was runny/salty. The chicken was the redeeming factor. Crispy on the outside and tender/juicy on the inside. The verde sauce!!! too good. If they could keep those sides fresh as the chicken, they would be a homerun.
